HEADWORD: Inhibitory-motor
<hw>In*hib"i*to*ry-mo"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A term applied to certain nerve centers which
govern or restrain subsidiary centers, from which motor impressions
issue.</def> <rj><au>McKendrick.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inhive</ent>⟦br⟧
